history.content: typically technical courses need more than six weeks.

Just wondering if anyone has heard of any useful summer session A courses for a CS/EECS major. All the ones I've seen have been non math/stat/cs/ee related. I'm going to audit it for personal learning, so I care mainly about usefulness, not much about workload.

Worst case, I'll take a course I'm interested in, like international finance, but if you have some cs-specific suggestions, I would love to hear them.
history.subject: Useful summer session A courses
